    <bioghist>Nelly Lewitt, married to John Lewitt, was an immigrant from England; she lived in Laingsburg, Michigan and elsewhere. John Lewitt was a taxidermist with the University of Michigan. He died in 1847. William Lewitt, John's brother, was an Ann Arbor druggist in the 1850s, attended the University of Michigan Dept. of Medicine and Surgery, 1853-1854, and served as Demonstrator of Anatomy in the department, 1858-1867. William Lewitt received his M.D. from Jefferson Medical College in 1857.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Letters received from the Lewitt family in Leicester, England, 1845-1848; letters to Nelly from her brother-in-law William Lewitt, 1847-1851; General Land Office certificate signed by President Martin Van Buren; also color photos of a squirrel prepared by John Lewitt.</scopecontent>
